# prj/

Intent v2.4.0 is a Bash-based CLI tool for managing "steel threads," self-contained work units that organize project artifacts and development planning. The project includes CLI commands, comprehensive BATS unit tests, shared libraries and templates, and extensive documentation. It supports plugins for agent management, skills distribution, and treeindex generation.

## Dirs

- `.github/` -- GitHub Actions workflows and CI/CD configuration
- `.intent/` -- Intent tool configuration and metadata
- `bin/` -- CLI entry points and command implementations
- `docs/` -- External documentation and deployment guides
- `examples/` -- Example Intent projects demonstrating best practices
- `intent/` -- Project artifacts, steel threads, work tracking, and LLM guidance
- `lib/` -- Shared library code and project templates
- `tests/` -- BATS unit test suites

## Files

- `CLAUDE.md` -- Project guidelines, command reference, and agent directory
- `README.md` -- Main documentation and project overview
- `CHANGELOG.md` -- Version history and release notes
- `_wip.md` -- Work in progress tracking and development context
